If you're wondering why HDFC Bank was the highest weightage stock in #Nifty50 for some time despite overall market cap being greater in RIL and TCS, it's because Nifty uses free-float market cap. It only considers the number of shares that are publicly available for trading.
The second most-weighted sector in Nifty is IT, with a mere 16.29%. Followed by oil & gas at 12.49% and consumer goods at 11.52%. Rest all are under 10%.

Weirdly enough, the proportion of HDFC twins to Top 5 is almost the same as the proportion of Top 5 to the entire Nifty 50. Aka, 42.41%. 

HDFC twins : Nifty Top 5 : : Nifty Top 5 : Nifty 50

Often times, HDFC Bank and HDFC (the HDFC twins) will move in a similar way. This means that they contribute nearly 18% of Nifty's moves. 

The same thing applies for the Bajaj Finance twins, except they have a slightly lower weightage.
The Top 5 stocks cumulatively account for 42.40% of the entire Nifty 50 index. The Top 10 account for 61.43%.
